}

// CORRECT — reads from the already-deep-merged content, so partial overrides preserve defaults
const content = deepMerge(defaultContent, overrides)
const get = useCallback((path: string) => {
  return deepGet(content, path)
}, [content])
```

This is a hydration-time bomb: SSR shows correct content (reads from defaults), then client hydration fetches overrides, `get()` returns a partial override that's missing sections, and the section unmounts after 1 second.

